data.title: Balkan Geography
data.text:
Geographical features, regions and cities in the Balkans

This much geographical knowledge is basic equipment for understanding the reading and lectures.

Try to pick it up as soon as you can from the Hupchick and Cox book, supplemented by a full-size atlas.

Especially useful is Paul Robert Magocsi, Historical Atlas of East Central Europe,

DJK4 .S93 1993 in the Olin reference collection.
